1
00:00:49,385 --> 00:00:53,785
<i>I'm just offering you a good option,</i>
<i>a life where you don't have to struggle.</i>

2
00:00:53,865 --> 00:00:57,305
A house, a car, anything you want,

3
00:00:57,385 --> 00:00:58,425
I can give it to you.

4
00:00:58,505 --> 00:01:01,585
What kind of person is Mr. Kritsana?

5
00:01:02,185 --> 00:01:03,545
Has he done something to you?

6
00:01:05,344 --> 00:01:07,545
With evidence this clear,

7
00:01:07,625 --> 00:01:08,505
how can you deny it?

8
00:01:08,585 --> 00:01:09,865
Oon, what's wrong?

9
00:01:09,945 --> 00:01:12,745
I can't build a future for you anymore.

10
00:01:12,825 --> 00:01:14,865
I've been suspended from work.

11
00:02:12,745 --> 00:02:15,225
What happened?
Did someone do something to Aioon?

12
00:02:16,465 --> 00:02:19,185
I don't know.
I just know it's about her work.

13
00:02:24,145 --> 00:02:28,145
-<i>Oon?</i>
-Fifa, it's me, Fun. Can you talk?

14
00:02:28,225 --> 00:02:29,905
Oh, yeah.

15
00:02:29,985 --> 00:02:32,345
What happened? Can you tell me everything?

16
00:02:35,025 --> 00:02:37,025
Some documents were sent to the company.

17
00:02:37,545 --> 00:02:41,505
<i>Then Nu said that</i>
<i>Oon and I were involved in fraud.</i>

18
00:02:51,865 --> 00:02:53,305
That's basically what happened.

19
00:02:54,465 --> 00:02:57,185
Then let's meet tomorrow at my place.

20
00:02:57,785 --> 00:02:59,305
What time works for you?

21
00:03:00,065 --> 00:03:01,265
Around 9 a.m.

22
00:03:01,985 --> 00:03:03,505
Okay, see you then.

23
00:03:05,625 --> 00:03:07,945
I don't believe it.
Aioon would never do something like that.

24
00:03:08,025 --> 00:03:11,545
I don't believe it either.
Someone has to be behind this.

25
00:03:33,665 --> 00:03:37,185
For now, you should get some rest.

26
00:03:38,145 --> 00:03:40,065
We'll figure it out tomorrow.

27
00:03:42,745 --> 00:03:43,905
Trust me.

28
00:04:14,705 --> 00:04:16,305
Can you think of anything else?

29
00:04:21,025 --> 00:04:24,625
This project was strange.
It got approved really fast.

30
00:04:24,705 --> 00:04:28,665
They requested me to be the designer
when we had never worked together before.

31
00:04:29,265 --> 00:04:32,585
Honestly,
I'm not that well-known in the industry.

32
00:04:32,665 --> 00:04:35,905
Exactly. If they wanted reputation,

33
00:04:35,985 --> 00:04:39,345
wouldn't Nu have been a better choice?
He's a certified professional engineer.

34
00:04:39,425 --> 00:04:40,425
True.

35
00:04:44,185 --> 00:04:46,705
Oh, and the other day, Mr. Kritsana

36
00:04:46,785 --> 00:04:49,985
was the one who called me to add
that paint company to the vendor list.

37
00:04:51,425 --> 00:04:54,105
Then Mr. Kritsana

38
00:04:54,185 --> 00:04:56,305
is definitely suspicious.

39
00:04:58,825 --> 00:05:01,265
Fifa, call him.

40
00:05:03,225 --> 00:05:05,425
Wait. Don't forget to record the call.

41
00:05:06,945 --> 00:05:09,145
MR. KRITSANA CONSULT

42
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:10,985
RECORDING WILL BEGIN
AFTER THE CALL IS CONNECTED

43
00:05:18,185 --> 00:05:20,865
Hello, Mr. Krit. Can you talk?

44
00:05:21,465 --> 00:05:22,945
What is it, Mr. Thanwa?

45
00:05:23,025 --> 00:05:25,425
Well, about

46
00:05:25,505 --> 00:05:28,985
the paint company
you asked me to add to the vendor list.

47
00:05:29,785 --> 00:05:31,505
What paint company?

48
00:05:31,585 --> 00:05:36,145
The one you urgently called me about,

49
00:05:36,225 --> 00:05:38,705
saying you'd send the memo later.

50
00:05:39,625 --> 00:05:42,145
<i>You must be mistaken. I never said that.</i>

51
00:05:43,385 --> 00:05:45,385
But…

52
00:05:45,465 --> 00:05:47,785
I don't have time for nonsense like this.

53
00:05:49,465 --> 00:05:52,225
Hey? What the heck? Oon.

54
00:05:52,305 --> 00:05:53,825
You were there that day.

55
00:05:53,905 --> 00:05:56,345
Yeah, what the heck?

56
00:06:02,585 --> 00:06:04,585
Oh, and there's more.

57
00:06:04,665 --> 00:06:07,505
The quotation was overpriced,

58
00:06:07,585 --> 00:06:10,905
and there were payments
from contractors too. I took photos.

59
00:06:14,105 --> 00:06:15,225
Here.

60
00:06:17,145 --> 00:06:19,785
Oh, that machine?
The one you asked me to check?

61
00:06:19,865 --> 00:06:22,825
Yeah. It's twice the normal price.

62
00:06:22,905 --> 00:06:26,825
That's seriously messed up.

63
00:06:27,545 --> 00:06:31,385
If he's denying it this shamelessly,
the only way is to get evidence from here.

64
00:06:33,065 --> 00:06:34,305
Then I'll call them.

65
00:06:48,625 --> 00:06:50,385
<i>Hello, Accounting Department.</i>

66
00:06:50,465 --> 00:06:51,505
Hello,

67
00:06:51,585 --> 00:06:55,385
I'd like to ask about a transfer
into Wirinya Sripitichote's account.

68
00:06:55,465 --> 00:06:56,545
May I ask who's calling?

69
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:58,225
Wirinya.

70
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:01,545
Oh?

71
00:07:02,305 --> 00:07:05,265
-Oon, don't bother calling anymore.
-Yeah, just go there.

72
00:07:05,345 --> 00:07:06,865
There are no other choices.

73
00:07:07,705 --> 00:07:08,585
-Let's go.
-Go.

74
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,865
Nueng, you stay here.

75
00:07:11,585 --> 00:07:13,945
Yes. You're pregnant.

76
00:07:14,785 --> 00:07:16,065
Fifa, come with me. Let's go.

77
00:07:22,585 --> 00:07:23,745
Are you okay?

78
00:07:26,185 --> 00:07:28,505
Yeah, go.

79
00:07:28,585 --> 00:07:29,785
-Don't worry about me.
-You sure?

80
00:07:29,865 --> 00:07:31,665
Yes. Just go.

81
00:07:31,745 --> 00:07:32,785
Go.

82
00:07:33,625 --> 00:07:35,745
Go. Don't worry about me. I can stay.

83
00:07:35,825 --> 00:07:37,065
Okay.

84
00:08:03,065 --> 00:08:05,545
-Hello.
-Hello.

85
00:08:06,385 --> 00:08:09,065
I'd like to meet the head of accounting.

86
00:08:09,145 --> 00:08:10,745
May I know your name?

87
00:08:10,825 --> 00:08:12,305
Wirinya.

88
00:08:12,865 --> 00:08:14,105
One moment, please.

89
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:20,745
Ms. Wirinya would like to meet you.

90
00:08:22,265 --> 00:08:24,145
Yes. Yes.

91
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:29,025
Please wait over here.

92
00:08:32,585 --> 00:08:34,065
This way, please.

93
00:09:16,145 --> 00:09:17,905
If you don't arrange for them to meet us,

94
00:09:18,505 --> 00:09:21,105
we will proceed with legal action.

95
00:09:22,025 --> 00:09:26,265
We will pursue this case to the end
without the possibility of a settlement.

96
00:09:27,265 --> 00:09:28,345
You have five minutes.

97
00:09:49,065 --> 00:09:50,265
Hello.

98
00:09:50,345 --> 00:09:54,345
The person who set the specifications
will explain everything.

99
00:10:10,225 --> 00:10:12,425
I want to know

100
00:10:12,505 --> 00:10:16,385
why your company
transferred money into my account.

101
00:10:17,065 --> 00:10:19,785
You're part of Mr. Kritsana's team, right?

102
00:10:19,865 --> 00:10:22,825
What do you mean by Mr. Kritsana's team?

103
00:10:22,905 --> 00:10:24,665
Yeah, what does that mean?

104
00:10:27,385 --> 00:10:29,585
Look, let me explain.

105
00:10:33,665 --> 00:10:38,305
I have a complex project. Interested in
getting your brand onto the vendor list?

106
00:10:38,905 --> 00:10:40,105
I am.

107
00:10:41,865 --> 00:10:43,865
But there's a processing fee.

108
00:10:43,945 --> 00:10:46,905
Please go ahead and name your price.

109
00:11:01,145 --> 00:11:02,105
Thirty thousand?

110
00:11:04,225 --> 00:11:05,505
Deal?

111
00:11:12,945 --> 00:11:14,665
I don't have much time.

112
00:11:19,425 --> 00:11:21,305
-I'll take that as your decision.
-Mr. Krit.

113
00:11:21,385 --> 00:11:22,905
Wait.

114
00:11:22,985 --> 00:11:27,225
Fine. I agree.

115
00:11:27,305 --> 00:11:30,025
I'll get your brand onto the vendor list.

116
00:11:31,105 --> 00:11:32,625
I'll send you the account number.

117
00:11:36,105 --> 00:11:37,265
That's evil.

118
00:11:41,545 --> 00:11:44,585
Do you realize
I had nothing to do with this?

119
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:48,465
How are you going to take responsibility?

120
00:11:49,905 --> 00:11:52,665
Maybe we should let the law handle this.

121
00:11:56,865 --> 00:11:58,425
Mr. Wasan,

122
00:11:58,505 --> 00:12:03,225
why don't you write a statement
and take your thirty thousand back?

123
00:12:05,065 --> 00:12:06,585
Excuse me,

124
00:12:06,665 --> 00:12:10,305
have you tried contacting Mr. Kritsana?

125
00:12:10,385 --> 00:12:11,545
Yes.

126
00:12:12,345 --> 00:12:14,185
He said he knows nothing.

127
00:12:14,785 --> 00:12:16,105
Nothing?

128
00:12:16,705 --> 00:12:18,505
How could he not know?

129
00:12:19,465 --> 00:12:20,785
Exactly.

130
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:23,585
That's what he said.

131
00:12:26,185 --> 00:12:29,505
Then I'll proceed with legal action
against your company

132
00:12:30,265 --> 00:12:33,625
for defamation.

133
00:12:36,185 --> 00:12:38,545
I'm not sure if this will help.

134
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:43,025
I have an audio recording

135
00:12:43,545 --> 00:12:44,745
of Mr. Kritsana.

136
00:12:47,745 --> 00:12:50,025
-Can we hear it?
-Yes.

137
00:12:51,985 --> 00:12:54,265
<i>Hello, is this Mr. Kritsana?</i>

138
00:12:54,345 --> 00:12:55,385
<i>Yes.</i>

139
00:12:55,905 --> 00:12:59,025
<i>The processing fee for the complex project</i>

140
00:12:59,625 --> 00:13:02,745
has to be transferred
to Ms. Wirinya Sripitichote's account.

141
00:13:02,825 --> 00:13:05,945
<i>30,000 baht. Is that all correct?</i>

142
00:13:06,545 --> 00:13:08,185
What's your problem?

143
00:13:08,265 --> 00:13:11,625
<i>I see that it's not your account,</i>

144
00:13:11,705 --> 00:13:14,625
<i>so I wanted to confirm the details again.</i>

145
00:13:16,705 --> 00:13:20,185
If you're going to be this difficult,
I'll remove your brand.

146
00:13:20,865 --> 00:13:23,265
Transfer it to where I told you.

147
00:13:28,025 --> 00:13:30,225
If you don't want this to escalate

148
00:13:30,305 --> 00:13:34,545
and you want to prove your innocence,
give us the recording.

149
00:13:34,625 --> 00:13:36,825
Yes, of course.

150
00:13:38,105 --> 00:13:39,425
Excuse me.

151
00:13:42,785 --> 00:13:45,345
I don't know how this will end.

152
00:13:46,265 --> 00:13:48,305
But let me give you a piece of advice.

153
00:13:50,425 --> 00:13:52,545
You shouldn't have done this.

154
00:13:53,225 --> 00:13:56,065
I've seen your intumescent paint.

155
00:13:56,145 --> 00:13:58,305
Your product meets the standards.

156
00:13:58,905 --> 00:14:02,505
You should present it honestly

157
00:14:02,585 --> 00:14:06,585
instead of bribing your way
onto the vendor list.

158
00:14:20,505 --> 00:14:22,505
Krit is too cunning.

159
00:14:22,585 --> 00:14:27,185
Even if we have an audio clip,
he'll say it's AI.

160
00:14:30,705 --> 00:14:32,825
We need video evidence.

161
00:14:33,945 --> 00:14:35,385
Then what do we do?

162
00:14:36,545 --> 00:14:39,065
-Let me be the bait.
-No.

163
00:14:39,945 --> 00:14:41,545
I don't want you going alone.

164
00:14:42,625 --> 00:14:44,785
Who said I'd go alone?

165
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:57,505
PAFUN

166
00:14:58,145 --> 00:15:00,865
So you've figured out who to choose.

167
00:15:06,305 --> 00:15:07,665
Yes, Fun?

168
00:15:08,425 --> 00:15:10,425
Do you have time to talk to me?

169
00:15:11,345 --> 00:15:12,305
<i>Sure.</i>

170
00:15:12,825 --> 00:15:16,345
Well, I need some advice.

171
00:15:16,985 --> 00:15:19,105
Can we meet?

172
00:15:19,785 --> 00:15:21,065
What is it about?

173
00:15:21,665 --> 00:15:24,105
About your old offer.

174
00:15:24,705 --> 00:15:27,025
I wonder if you still remember it.

175
00:15:28,145 --> 00:15:30,545
Of course. What time works for you?

176
00:15:33,225 --> 00:15:37,185
Can we meet now? I'll send the location.

177
00:15:37,785 --> 00:15:39,025
<i>Sure.</i>

178
00:15:39,625 --> 00:15:40,745
See you.

179
00:15:43,585 --> 00:15:45,385
I seriously want to rip his hair out.

180
00:15:47,545 --> 00:15:49,745
In the end, you chose me.

181
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:00,985
<i>I'm parked on the second floor,</i>

182
00:16:01,065 --> 00:16:03,625
<i>Pillar N45.</i>

183
00:16:03,705 --> 00:16:05,185
<i>You can park next to me.</i>

184
00:16:15,505 --> 00:16:16,465
Krit.

185
00:16:19,185 --> 00:16:20,585
Nice car.

186
00:16:22,345 --> 00:16:23,625
You want one?

187
00:16:24,505 --> 00:16:27,345
I'm thinking about it.

188
00:16:30,185 --> 00:16:33,225
Can I borrow your keys?

189
00:16:39,625 --> 00:16:43,945
Once we're done tonight,
you can get your new car tomorrow.

190
00:17:19,704 --> 00:17:21,305
What are you trying to do?

191
00:17:21,825 --> 00:17:23,224
What about you?

192
00:17:26,184 --> 00:17:28,985
-<i>Hello, is this Mr. Kritsana?</i>
-<i>Yes.</i>

193
00:17:29,065 --> 00:17:31,705
<i>The processing fee for the complex project</i>

194
00:17:31,785 --> 00:17:35,145
<i>has to be transferred</i>
<i>to Ms. Wirinya Sripitichote's account…</i>

195
00:17:37,105 --> 00:17:38,465
You teamed up?

196
00:17:39,065 --> 00:17:40,145
Did you do it?

197
00:17:42,305 --> 00:17:45,265
Yeah. So what?

198
00:17:45,345 --> 00:17:48,705
Who would believe you?
I'll just say it's AI.

199
00:17:49,545 --> 00:17:52,985
Then what about this invoice?

200
00:17:53,065 --> 00:17:54,465
AI too?

201
00:17:55,145 --> 00:17:56,185
Yeah. So what?

202
00:17:56,785 --> 00:17:58,745
And the bribe from contractors?

203
00:18:05,225 --> 00:18:06,505
Park the car and come here.

204
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:10,785
Mr. Krit.

205
00:18:14,905 --> 00:18:16,105
Here it is.

206
00:18:19,505 --> 00:18:20,745
There's one more client left.

207
00:18:23,625 --> 00:18:24,905
<i>Which one?</i>

208
00:18:24,985 --> 00:18:26,425
Air duct.

209
00:18:26,505 --> 00:18:27,425
<i>You can go now.</i>

210
00:18:41,185 --> 00:18:43,425
Yeah, I did all of it.

211
00:18:43,945 --> 00:18:45,465
But what can you do

212
00:18:46,065 --> 00:18:49,945
with evidence like this?
Who'd be stupid enough to believe you?

213
00:18:50,985 --> 00:18:54,385
Let me tell you something.

214
00:18:54,465 --> 00:18:56,065
There are no CCTV cameras around here.

215
00:18:57,825 --> 00:19:02,465
I'm a consultant,
while you're just engineers.

216
00:19:02,545 --> 00:19:04,785
The owner will obviously believe me
more than you.

217
00:19:04,865 --> 00:19:05,945
And besides,

218
00:19:06,745 --> 00:19:09,665
the evidence clearly shows
the money went into your account.

219
00:19:12,665 --> 00:19:16,985
You really have no dignity. Maybe you
should borrow Aunt Sa-Ngad's skirt.

220
00:19:17,065 --> 00:19:18,865
You've got such a mouth.
Let me teach you a lesson.

221
00:19:22,745 --> 00:19:24,305
-You!
-Go ahead.

222
00:19:43,185 --> 00:19:44,185
Fun, please.

223
00:19:46,385 --> 00:19:48,025
For the sake of our friendship.

224
00:19:48,985 --> 00:19:52,185
I did all of this
because I wanted to marry you.

225
00:19:54,305 --> 00:19:55,585
Delete that clip.

226
00:19:56,545 --> 00:19:58,665
I'll fix Aioon's situation

227
00:19:59,665 --> 00:20:01,145
and make it like
none of this ever happened.

228
00:20:02,225 --> 00:20:03,345
Disgusting.

229
00:20:04,065 --> 00:20:08,025
Before this, you said I didn't have
to leave Aioon just have fun with you.

230
00:20:08,785 --> 00:20:11,505
And now you're saying
you want to marry me?

231
00:20:12,425 --> 00:20:15,625
Fun, I'm sorry.

232
00:20:15,705 --> 00:20:17,865
Tell me how much you want.

233
00:20:17,945 --> 00:20:19,825
I'll give you anything. I have plenty.

234
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:22,025
I'll write you a check right now.

235
00:20:22,625 --> 00:20:24,025
-Or cash?
-Let me give this to you.

236
00:20:27,425 --> 00:20:30,545
We're not just filing a police report.
We'll inform the owner

237
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:32,145
and the company too.

238
00:20:32,665 --> 00:20:34,945
And if you think no one will believe us,
go ahead and try.

239
00:21:15,505 --> 00:21:16,705
Damn it!

240
00:21:47,145 --> 00:21:50,705
Is it happening again?
Do you want me to sleep here with you?

241
00:21:52,185 --> 00:21:54,705
It's okay. It'll get better.

242
00:22:05,305 --> 00:22:06,905
If you can't handle it, call me.

243
00:22:34,265 --> 00:22:35,785
Is Nubnueng asleep?

244
00:22:36,745 --> 00:22:37,705
Yes.

245
00:22:50,185 --> 00:22:54,225
Go shower.
I'll gather the evidence while I wait.

246
00:23:23,825 --> 00:23:25,265
Fun…

247
00:23:38,185 --> 00:23:40,065
If I

248
00:23:40,745 --> 00:23:43,745
couldn't find the evidence
to prove my innocence…

249
00:23:45,585 --> 00:23:48,305
if I couldn't be an engineer…

250
00:23:50,265 --> 00:23:54,265
if I couldn't take care of our family…

251
00:23:55,745 --> 00:23:57,345
and if I couldn't--

252
00:24:03,065 --> 00:24:04,825
I would still love you.

253
00:24:05,465 --> 00:24:07,665
That's a truth that won't change.

254
00:24:11,545 --> 00:24:15,265
I don't know when I fell in love with you.

255
00:24:16,825 --> 00:24:19,905
I just realized one day
that I already had.

256
00:24:22,905 --> 00:24:24,345
So,

257
00:24:25,585 --> 00:24:27,825
whether you can do it or not,

258
00:24:30,185 --> 00:24:32,385
you're still you,

259
00:24:34,705 --> 00:24:36,265
the person I fell in love with.

260
00:24:55,225 --> 00:24:58,545
Thank you for trusting me.

261
00:25:25,265 --> 00:25:26,745
EVIDENCE

262
00:25:26,825 --> 00:25:30,345
EVIDENCE

263
00:25:30,425 --> 00:25:34,025
I've sent all the evidence
to your email, Nu.

264
00:25:35,705 --> 00:25:39,945
Okay, I got it.
I'll forward it to HR right away.

265
00:25:40,025 --> 00:25:41,865
I'll call you
as soon as there's an update.

266
00:25:41,945 --> 00:25:45,225
Okay. Thank you, Nu. Goodbye.

267
00:25:50,625 --> 00:25:54,465
With evidence this clear,
Krit won't get away with it.

268
00:25:55,025 --> 00:25:57,105
He can kiss his future goodbye.

269
00:25:57,745 --> 00:26:00,265
Such a shame. If I'd gone that day,

270
00:26:00,345 --> 00:26:03,065
he would've met my foot too.

271
00:26:03,865 --> 00:26:06,265
Pregnant lady, calm down.

272
00:26:09,225 --> 00:26:12,105
Well, when's
your next doctor's appointment?

273
00:26:12,945 --> 00:26:15,225
-This Friday.
-This Friday?

274
00:26:18,505 --> 00:26:20,145
In just a few months,
we'll get to meet the little one.

275
00:26:22,825 --> 00:26:26,385
So, what should the little one call me?

276
00:26:26,905 --> 00:26:29,905
My mom is your older cousin,

277
00:26:29,985 --> 00:26:31,585
so technically I'm your niece.

278
00:26:31,665 --> 00:26:34,505
That means my baby
should call you Grandma. Grandma Oon.

279
00:26:34,585 --> 00:26:37,785
Nueng, I'm not that old.

280
00:26:37,865 --> 00:26:39,225
And you

281
00:26:39,305 --> 00:26:40,665
-should be…
-Stop.

282
00:26:41,585 --> 00:26:43,145
Don't say it.

283
00:26:43,945 --> 00:26:45,665
Fine, I won't say it. Granny.

284
00:26:45,745 --> 00:26:46,825
Nueng.

285
00:26:49,305 --> 00:26:50,745
I'll wait until after you give birth.

286
00:26:53,185 --> 00:26:57,065
I'll have the little one call me Mommy.

287
00:26:57,825 --> 00:26:59,425
Mommy.

288
00:26:59,505 --> 00:27:00,545
Then what about me?

289
00:27:01,265 --> 00:27:04,785
If the little one calls you Mommy,
what should they call me?

290
00:27:04,865 --> 00:27:07,065
Mommy too.

291
00:27:07,145 --> 00:27:09,145
Mommy Fun. Mommy Oon.

292
00:27:19,145 --> 00:27:20,265
Please have a seat.

293
00:27:23,905 --> 00:27:28,465
I owe you an apology, Ms. Wirinya,
Mr. Thanwa, and to your company, Mr. Nu,

294
00:27:28,545 --> 00:27:31,025
for all the damage this has caused.

295
00:27:31,105 --> 00:27:34,625
It's alright.
I won't pursue anything against you.

296
00:27:35,225 --> 00:27:38,825
We were all victims in this.

297
00:27:38,905 --> 00:27:42,785
My lawyer has already filed
a police report against Mr. Kritsana.

298
00:27:43,385 --> 00:27:46,105
The police have issued an arrest warrant
and are tracking him down.

299
00:27:46,185 --> 00:27:49,505
I've spoken
to the detective handling the case.

300
00:27:49,585 --> 00:27:53,505
They expect to bring him in
to face legal action very soon.

301
00:27:57,105 --> 00:27:59,905
-Alright.
-Thank you.

302
00:28:06,145 --> 00:28:10,025
Thank you, Nu, for helping us.

303
00:28:12,545 --> 00:28:13,385
Well, Oon,

304
00:28:13,465 --> 00:28:17,905
about your professional license test,
how's your portfolio?

305
00:28:18,745 --> 00:28:20,585
It should be complete
by the end of this month.

306
00:28:20,665 --> 00:28:22,905
-I'm rooting for you.
-Thank you.

307
00:28:22,985 --> 00:28:25,305
Alright, back to work.

308
00:29:02,265 --> 00:29:06,585
UPDATE THE COORDINATES
FOR THIS POINT AS WELL

309
00:29:10,425 --> 00:29:14,905
PROFESSIONAL ENGINEER
LICENSE PROMOTION INTERVIEW

310
00:29:52,665 --> 00:29:55,345
-Here, warm milk.
-Thanks.

311
00:29:55,945 --> 00:29:58,065
-What are you watching?
-This. I'm checking this out.

312
00:30:04,385 --> 00:30:07,145
Oon-Oon, are you free tomorrow?

313
00:30:07,665 --> 00:30:09,665
Tomorrow?

314
00:30:09,745 --> 00:30:13,865
No, I'm not. I have meetings
with Mr. Anan's team all day.

315
00:30:13,945 --> 00:30:15,465
Why?

316
00:30:16,825 --> 00:30:19,665
Nueng has her checkup tomorrow,

317
00:30:19,745 --> 00:30:21,585
but no one's free to go with her.

318
00:30:22,105 --> 00:30:25,025
I have to go receive
a client brief on-site.

319
00:30:25,105 --> 00:30:28,425
Hey, did you guys forget something?

320
00:30:28,505 --> 00:30:31,105
I lived alone for years abroad.

321
00:30:31,185 --> 00:30:33,985
Going to the hospital alone is easy.
No need.

322
00:30:35,705 --> 00:30:39,065
Then how about this?
My meeting is at eleven.

323
00:30:39,145 --> 00:30:41,825
I'll drop you off first,

324
00:30:41,905 --> 00:30:43,905
but I might not be able
to stay until you're done.

325
00:30:44,905 --> 00:30:48,505
Actually, you don't have to.
I can go alone.

326
00:30:49,105 --> 00:30:52,665
Don't make me worry, okay?

327
00:30:52,745 --> 00:30:55,745
Fine, fine. Do whatever you want.

328
00:30:55,825 --> 00:30:57,585
If you want to go, then go.

329
00:30:57,665 --> 00:30:58,985
Let me see that.

330
00:31:00,305 --> 00:31:01,625
What is it?

331
00:31:08,665 --> 00:31:09,665
So pretty.

332
00:31:24,305 --> 00:31:25,185
Here.

333
00:31:27,905 --> 00:31:30,305
Hey!

334
00:31:31,025 --> 00:31:32,385
Nueng.

335
00:31:35,025 --> 00:31:36,745
You spilled it.

336
00:31:39,785 --> 00:31:40,905
Let me see.

337
00:31:55,305 --> 00:31:57,505
Good job. Here, take a tissue.

338
00:31:59,505 --> 00:32:01,545
Well, I have to go now.

339
00:32:01,625 --> 00:32:04,465
Yeah, go ahead. I'll be fine alone.

340
00:32:04,545 --> 00:32:05,825
-Are you sure?
-Sure.

341
00:32:06,985 --> 00:32:08,265
-Okay.
-Don't worry.

342
00:32:08,345 --> 00:32:09,905
-Bye.
-Bye. Good luck.

343
00:32:19,585 --> 00:32:22,065
Ms. Kanyavee, please come in.

344
00:32:22,145 --> 00:32:23,345
Okay.

345
00:32:39,185 --> 00:32:41,185
Congratulations.

346
00:32:41,265 --> 00:32:44,105
The baby's heart rate is normal.

347
00:32:44,185 --> 00:32:47,385
The baby is healthy
and developing well for its age.

348
00:33:04,865 --> 00:33:07,225
Nueng, please tell the driver

349
00:33:07,305 --> 00:33:09,265
to wait for me.
I'm going to the district office.

350
00:33:09,345 --> 00:33:11,625
Okay. Please wait a moment.

351
00:33:11,705 --> 00:33:13,145
Are you going to make an ID card?

352
00:33:13,225 --> 00:33:15,945
No, I'm going to make a will.

353
00:33:16,825 --> 00:33:18,145
A will? At the district office?

354
00:33:18,225 --> 00:33:20,985
These days, you can do it there too.

355
00:33:21,065 --> 00:33:25,065
There have been some inheritance disputes
in my hometown,

356
00:33:25,145 --> 00:33:27,345
so I want to settle everything.

357
00:33:27,425 --> 00:33:30,305
I'll transfer everything to Pa.

358
00:33:30,385 --> 00:33:32,905
That's it. So, where did you go?

359
00:33:32,985 --> 00:33:36,785
I went to the hospital.
I had an appointment.

360
00:33:36,865 --> 00:33:38,665
Okay. I'll go now.

361
00:33:41,865 --> 00:33:44,905
Aunt Wi, can I go with you?

362
00:33:44,985 --> 00:33:48,105
I want to make a will too.
What documents do I need?

363
00:33:48,185 --> 00:33:52,065
Just your ID card and house registration.

364
00:33:52,705 --> 00:33:54,785
But I don't have my house registration.

365
00:33:57,425 --> 00:34:00,105
Everything can be done
at the district office now.

366
00:34:00,185 --> 00:34:02,505
You can request a copy at the counter.

367
00:34:02,585 --> 00:34:06,465
With me around, there's no need to worry.
I'm good at this. Okay?

368
00:34:06,545 --> 00:34:07,545
Okay.

369
00:34:07,625 --> 00:34:08,744
Get back in.

370
00:34:08,824 --> 00:34:09,705
Okay.

371
00:34:13,545 --> 00:34:14,705
Let's go.

372
00:34:18,425 --> 00:34:19,665
Fifa.

373
00:34:24,824 --> 00:34:26,665
What happened to your neck?

374
00:34:27,185 --> 00:34:29,264
Slept wrong. It's stiff.

375
00:34:30,505 --> 00:34:32,145
How do you even sleep like that?

376
00:34:33,545 --> 00:34:34,784
Did you see a doctor?

377
00:34:34,865 --> 00:34:38,185
Yeah. I took the morning off
and just got back.

378
00:34:39,264 --> 00:34:40,865
-Good.
-Yeah.

379
00:34:40,945 --> 00:34:43,665
Oh, yeah, I saw your girlfriend

380
00:34:43,744 --> 00:34:46,385
and your relative at the hospital.
The pregnant one.

381
00:34:47,824 --> 00:34:50,185
-Oh, Nubnueng.
-Yeah, that one.

382
00:34:50,264 --> 00:34:52,304
I don't remember names well.

383
00:34:52,385 --> 00:34:56,705
If I didn't know Pafun was your
girlfriend, I'd think they were a couple.

384
00:34:58,625 --> 00:35:02,305
You're crazy.
Fun just likes taking care of people.

385
00:35:02,825 --> 00:35:04,825
And Nubnueng is my relative.

386
00:35:04,905 --> 00:35:07,665
Yeah, yeah, just kidding.

387
00:35:08,265 --> 00:35:11,105
You should go get your mouth treated too.

388
00:35:11,185 --> 00:35:12,425
-Huh?
-Yeah,

389
00:35:12,505 --> 00:35:14,025
sounds like a potty mouth.

390
00:35:17,185 --> 00:35:18,425
Just kidding.

391
00:35:20,345 --> 00:35:22,505
Yeah, I'm going back to work.
I was just kidding, yeah?

392
00:35:22,585 --> 00:35:24,465
-Get well soon.
-Thanks.

393
00:35:37,345 --> 00:35:41,385
Jay, can you recheck this for me?

394
00:35:52,145 --> 00:35:55,425
Wow, what did you buy? That's a lot.

395
00:35:59,385 --> 00:36:00,745
Come on, I'll help.

396
00:36:01,545 --> 00:36:05,265
-Come, I already unwrapped the fish.
-What's the occasion?

397
00:36:05,345 --> 00:36:07,185
You'll see. Here, the plate.

398
00:36:09,145 --> 00:36:11,305
-It should be bamboo soup.
-Smells so good.

399
00:36:13,345 --> 00:36:15,585
That's a lot. I'm hungry already.

400
00:36:19,465 --> 00:36:21,585
Pour it slowly. Be careful not to spill.

401
00:36:21,665 --> 00:36:23,145
Hey, what's that box?

402
00:36:27,025 --> 00:36:28,065
What?

403
00:36:34,265 --> 00:36:35,625
What is it?

404
00:36:35,705 --> 00:36:39,105
So, I already know if our baby

405
00:36:39,185 --> 00:36:41,065
is a boy or a girl.

406
00:36:56,665 --> 00:36:58,985
Does anyone want to guess first?

407
00:36:59,585 --> 00:37:00,985
Me?

408
00:37:01,985 --> 00:37:03,665
I think…

409
00:37:05,345 --> 00:37:06,225
a boy.

410
00:37:06,305 --> 00:37:07,745
A boy?

411
00:37:09,625 --> 00:37:12,265
For me, either is fine.

412
00:37:15,145 --> 00:37:17,545
Okay, let's reveal it.

413
00:37:18,425 --> 00:37:20,225
-Ready?
-Ready.

414
00:37:20,305 --> 00:37:22,785
-Calm down.
-One!

415
00:37:23,585 --> 00:37:26,185
One, two, three!

416
00:37:37,945 --> 00:37:39,425
A boy!

417
00:37:39,505 --> 00:37:42,465
A boy! We got a boy!

418
00:37:49,145 --> 00:37:50,505
A boy.

419
00:37:51,065 --> 00:37:54,145
Look at this first. Let me show you.

420
00:37:54,225 --> 00:37:55,345
Do you know what this is?

421
00:37:56,305 --> 00:37:57,705
The ultrasound.

422
00:37:58,265 --> 00:38:00,945
-The baby.
-At first, I thought if it's a girl,

423
00:38:01,025 --> 00:38:03,305
I'd name her Nanfah,

424
00:38:03,385 --> 00:38:06,785
but if it's a boy, I'd name him Phupha,

425
00:38:06,865 --> 00:38:09,145
so he'd be strong like a mountain,

426
00:38:09,225 --> 00:38:10,945
no matter the storm.

427
00:38:14,905 --> 00:38:16,305
Phupha,

428
00:38:16,385 --> 00:38:18,865
we'll meet you soon.

429
00:38:19,865 --> 00:38:22,065
Come out and meet us soon, okay?

430
00:39:46,745 --> 00:39:49,945
<i>I saw your girlfriend</i>
<i>and your relative at the hospital.</i>

431
00:39:50,585 --> 00:39:52,905
<i>If I didn't know</i>
<i>Pafun was your girlfriend,</i>

432
00:39:52,985 --> 00:39:54,985
<i>I'd think they were a couple.</i>

433
00:40:12,105 --> 00:40:13,385
Oon.

434
00:40:13,465 --> 00:40:14,985
I want to have a baby.

435
00:41:23,145 --> 00:41:24,625
Aren't you going to eat breakfast?

436
00:41:26,105 --> 00:41:27,865
We already ate. Go ahead and eat.

437
00:42:18,545 --> 00:42:19,985
I'm heading to work.

438
00:42:21,665 --> 00:42:22,865
I'll check on her.

439
00:42:31,465 --> 00:42:33,505
You barely ate.

440
00:42:34,705 --> 00:42:36,705
I'm late. I'll go now.

441
00:42:51,825 --> 00:42:58,425
DAY OF PROFESSIONAL ENGINEER LICENSE
PROMOTION RESULT ANNOUNCEMENT

442
00:43:12,465 --> 00:43:13,785
I passed!

443
00:43:36,985 --> 00:43:38,745
<i>Hello.</i>

444
00:43:44,705 --> 00:43:45,665
That's funny.

445
00:43:58,585 --> 00:44:00,705
Watching in the dark like this
will ruin your eyesight.

446
00:44:03,705 --> 00:44:05,945
Oon-oon.

447
00:44:08,225 --> 00:44:09,305
Go.

448
00:44:27,345 --> 00:44:28,665
Aren't you hungry?

449
00:44:31,305 --> 00:44:32,505
No.

450
00:44:35,545 --> 00:44:37,105
When will you be?

451
00:44:38,825 --> 00:44:42,985
Whenever. I'll handle it myself.

452
00:44:44,145 --> 00:44:45,585
Go watch your movie.

453
00:44:52,905 --> 00:44:53,945
It hurts.

454
00:44:59,145 --> 00:45:00,185
Are you jealous?

455
00:45:02,345 --> 00:45:04,145
No. Why would I be?

456
00:45:07,025 --> 00:45:08,905
Then why won't you look at me?

457
00:45:10,545 --> 00:45:13,265
If you don't talk, I'll get mad.

458
00:45:23,305 --> 00:45:24,465
I don't know.

459
00:45:25,545 --> 00:45:27,705
I just don't like what I see.

460
00:45:29,385 --> 00:45:32,105
Don't like what? Don't like me?

461
00:45:32,985 --> 00:45:35,105
No.

462
00:45:36,025 --> 00:45:40,545
I just don't like how I feel right now.

463
00:45:49,305 --> 00:45:50,705
Why are you smiling?

464
00:45:53,025 --> 00:45:54,785
Because I know

465
00:45:55,345 --> 00:45:57,225
you're like this

466
00:45:58,145 --> 00:45:59,945
because you care about me.

467
00:46:07,025 --> 00:46:08,265
Better?

468
00:46:15,465 --> 00:46:16,385
Better?

469
00:46:22,825 --> 00:46:25,305
-Better?
-I'm better now.

470
00:46:34,105 --> 00:46:34,905
Fun.

471
00:46:36,305 --> 00:46:39,185
I passed the promotion exam.

472
00:46:39,945 --> 00:46:41,545
Really?

473
00:46:43,585 --> 00:46:45,305
Congrats!

474
00:46:45,385 --> 00:46:47,265
You're amazing.

475
00:46:48,025 --> 00:46:49,545
That means

476
00:46:50,545 --> 00:46:54,705
from now on, I'm ready.

477
00:46:54,785 --> 00:46:58,265
If you want to quit your job
and start your own company,

478
00:46:58,345 --> 00:46:59,305
you can.

479
00:47:04,745 --> 00:47:06,385
Then you deserve a reward.

480
00:47:44,745 --> 00:47:47,025
Oon-oon, how much cash
do you have left right now?

481
00:47:47,105 --> 00:47:48,265
Around 500 baht.

482
00:47:48,345 --> 00:47:51,385
Then make it last until the end
of the month. I'm not giving you more.

483
00:47:53,825 --> 00:47:55,385
I think my water broke.

484
00:47:55,465 --> 00:47:56,425
‎Your water broke?

485
00:47:56,505 --> 00:47:58,745
‎Oon, The car keys aren't that way.

486
00:47:58,825 --> 00:47:59,745
‎Oh, right.

487
00:48:05,265 --> 00:48:08,865
So this is what they mean
by beautiful pain.

488
00:48:08,945 --> 00:48:14,105
Welcome to Mommies' family, Phupha.

489
00:48:37,065 --> 00:48:40,705
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon

